Testing Procedure
The system was tested by:
•	Adding menu items 
•	Searching for items 
•	Placing multiple orders 
•	Removing items 
•	Generating bills 
•	Testing invalid inputs 
All functionalities produced the expected results.

5. Reflection
Challenges Encountered
Faced several challenges in the development phase: 
•	Designing relationships between classes. 
•	Managing interactions between Menu, Order, and Bill classes.
•	Implementing bill calculations accurately.
Lessons Learned
Through this project, the following concepts were learned:
•	Class and object creation.
•	Encapsulation and modular programming.
•	Method implementation. 
•	List manipulation.
•	User input handling. 
•	Program organization using multiple files. 
Future Improvements
Possible future enhancements include:
•	Storing menu items using CSV files 
•	Maintaining order history 
•	Database integration using MySQL 
•	Customer account management 
•	Online order processing 
Conclusion
The Restaurant Order and Billing Management System successfully automates menu management, order processing, and bill generation. The project demonstrates the practical application of Python programming and Object-Oriented Programming concepts in solving real-world business problems.

